  "prompt": "Can I claim HRA during ITR Filing?",
  "response": "Yes, you can claim House Rent Allowance (HRA) when filing your Income Tax Return (ITR) in India, provided you meet certain conditions. Here's a brief overview of how you can do this:\n\n1. **Eligibility:** You must be a salaried employee receiving HRA as part of your salary, and you should be paying rent for residential accommodation.\n\n2. **Documentation:** You should have rent receipts or a rent agreement as proof of your rental expenses. If your annual rent exceeds \u20b91 lakh, you must provide the landlord's PAN details.\n\n3. **Calculation:** The amount you can claim as HRA exemption will be the least of the following:\n   - Actual HRA received.\n   - 50% of basic salary if you live in a metro city (40% for non-metro cities).\n   - Actual rent paid minus 10% of basic salary.\n\n4. **Form 16:** Ensure your employer includes the details of HRA exemption in Form 16, which you need for filing your ITR.\n\n5. **Form 10BA:** If you are not able to claim HRA through your employer but are eligible otherwise, you can claim it while filing your ITR using Form 10BA.\n\nBy following these guidelines, you can claim HRA exemption accurately when filing your ITR.",
